Class DistributionView

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node

no.ntnu.idatx1005.view.content.DistributionView
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget, ButtonClickSubject
public class DistributionView extends javafx.scene.layout.HBox implements ButtonClickSubject

View for the distribution view.

The view is meant to be used as a child of the ContentView class. The view is a HBox that contains two VBox containers: one for the available users and one for the unassigned tasks. It implements the ButtonClickSubject interface to notify observers when a button in the view is clicked.

Since:
V1.1.0
Author:
William Holtsdalen
